<section class="product-desc-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="product-desc-grid">
      <div class="product-desc">
        <div class="section-tag">Product Overview</div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <h2>Engineered for the <span>Toughest</span> Downhole Conditions</h2>
        <p>Our drilling grade sepiolite is a specially processed rheology modifier designed for oil and gas drilling fluid applications. Unlike bentonite, sepiolite maintains its viscosity-building properties in saturated salt solutions and at temperatures exceeding 200°C — conditions that cause bentonite to flocculate and lose effectiveness.</p>
        <p>The product meets API Specification 13A requirements for drilling-grade sepiolite and is routinely used in geothermal wells, deep offshore operations, and salt dome drilling. Its unique fibrous structure creates a three-dimensional network in drilling fluid that provides excellent hole-cleaning and cuttings suspension.</p>
        <p>Drilling grade sepiolite also contributes to wellbore stability by forming a thin, low-permeability filter cake on the borehole wall. This reduces fluid loss to the formation and helps maintain wellbore integrity in problematic shale and unconsolidated sand intervals.</p>
        <p>We supply drilling grade sepiolite to major oilfield service companies and national oil companies worldwide. Our product is backed by detailed technical data sheets and field performance reports for specific well conditions upon request.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="tech-specs-card">
          <h3>
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M10 2L18 7V13L10 18L2 13V7L10 2Z" stroke="#C9922A" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="3" fill="#C9922A"/></svg>
            Technical Specifications
          </h3>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Product Form</span>
            <span class="spec-value">Fine Powder</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">API Specification</span>
            <span class="spec-value">13A Compliant</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Thermal Stability</span>
            <span class="spec-value">Up to 300°C</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Yield Point (6% slurry)</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≥ 15 lb/100ft²</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Plastic Viscosity</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≥ 10 cP</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">MgO</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≥ 18%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">SiO₂</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≥ 54%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Moisture</span>
            <span class="spec-value">≤ 10%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Salt Tolerance</span>
            <span class="spec-value">Saturated NaCl</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Particle Size</span>
            <span class="spec-value">95% < 75μm</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Packaging</span>
            <span class="spec-value">25kg Multi-wall Bags</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-row">
            <span class="spec-label">Delivery</span>
            <span class="spec-value">FOB Mersin / Samsun</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="usage-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="usage-header">
      <div class="section-tag" style="color:var(--gold-light);">Applications</div>
      <div class="divider divider--center"></div>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="color:var(--white);">Where Drilling Grade Sepiolite <span>Is Used</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="usage-grid">
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🛢️</div>
        <h3>Geothermal Drilling</h3>
        <p>Essential in geothermal wells where temperatures exceed 200°C and bentonite-based muds break down. Sepiolite maintains rheology throughout the drilling operation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🌊</div>
        <h3>Offshore Deep Water</h3>
        <p>Used in deepwater drilling operations where high hydrostatic pressures and temperature gradients demand a thermally stable viscosifier for safe and efficient operations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🧂</div>
        <h3>Salt Dome Operations</h3>
        <p>The go-to viscosifier for drilling through salt formations. Unlike bentonite, sepiolite performs identically in fresh water and saturated brine systems.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🔧</div>
        <h3>Horizontal Directional Drilling</h3>
        <p>Provides excellent hole-cleaning properties in extended-reach and horizontal wells where cuttings transport is critical for preventing stuck pipe.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🏗️</div>
        <h3>Foundation & Piling</h3>
        <p>Used in large-diameter bored pile and diaphragm wall construction. Sepiolite drilling fluids stabilize excavations in challenging ground conditions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="usage-card reveal">
        <div class="usage-icon">🌍</div>
        <h3>Environmental Drilling</h3>
        <p>Deployed in environmental site investigation and remediation wells. The natural, non-toxic mineral is preferred in sensitive ecological areas.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="advantages-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="advantages-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="section-tag">Why Choose Us</div>
        <div class="divider"></div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Key <span>Advantages</span></h2>
        <div class="advantage-list">
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">01</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Unmatched Thermal Stability</strong>
              <p>Maintains full rheological performance up to 300°C — critical for geothermal, deep offshore, and HPHT well applications.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">02</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Complete Salt Tolerance</strong>
              <p>Unlike bentonite, sepiolite performs identically in fresh water, seawater, and saturated NaCl brine. No performance loss in salt formations.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">03</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Superior Hole Cleaning</strong>
              <p>The fibrous structure creates a pseudo-plastic fluid system with excellent shear-thinning behavior, providing efficient cuttings transport.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">04</div>
            <div>
              <strong>Low Fluid Loss</strong>
              <p>Forms a thin, impermeable filter cake on the wellbore wall, reducing drilling fluid invasion into permeable formations.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-item reveal">
            <div class="advantage-num">05</div>
            <div>
              <strong>API-Certified Quality</strong>
              <p>Every batch is tested to API 13A specifications. Full technical data and performance certificates provided with each shipment.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="advantage-image">
        <img width="960" height="1280" src="/images/mine/mine-landscape-11.webp" alt="Sepiolite mine – Zamana Turkey" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="faq-header">
      <div class="section-tag">Common Questions</div>
      <div class="divider divider--center"></div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked <span>Questions</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Does your drilling grade sepiolite meet API specifications?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Yes, our product is manufactured and tested to meet API Specification 13A requirements. Certificates of compliance are provided with every shipment.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          At what temperature does sepiolite outperform bentonite?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Sepiolite maintains stable rheology up to 300°C, while bentonite typically begins to flocculate above 120°C. Above 150°C, sepiolite is the clear choice.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What is the recommended concentration for drilling fluids?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Typical concentrations range from 2–6% by weight depending on required rheology. Our technical team can provide optimized formulations for your specific well conditions.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          Can sepiolite be used alongside other drilling fluid additives?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Yes, sepiolite is compatible with most standard drilling fluid additives including polymers, lubricants, and fluid loss control agents. Contact us for compatibility guidance.
        </div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
          What is the minimum order for drilling grade sepiolite?
          <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M5 7.5L10 12.5L15 7.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">
          Minimum order is 20 metric tons. For oilfield service companies with regular requirements, we offer annual supply agreements with volume discounts.
        </div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="related-section">
